      "weather": "showers",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SENSHI (5) finally drawn a decent gate and due for a change of luck. Covered a stack of ground in the run with a fast finishing second over 1100m at Gosford. Can tick off the 1200m box today with the fast tempo anticipated. HARLEX (3) lightly raced gelding resuming with a good fresh record. Wasn't pushed out in the two trials and has a host of gear changes from the good gate. Genuine top-three player who will prove hard to run down. FLORINO (1) lines up for the new yard off the back of two sharp trials. Well in with Llewellyn's 3kg claim and brings the right credentials to take this out.  PRATT (2) consistent sprinter ready to win at his third run back. Faded late in a solid contest when third to Pony Soprano over 1106m at Port Macquarie in BM74 grade. Maps well and expected to go close.",
